Notes:

Although HEAD is not explicitly registered, many HTTP servers treat HEAD requests to a path with a GET handler as valid (the framework serves the same response with the body omitted). Since a GET handler exists, HEAD is considered acceptable based on standard HTTP behavior, even though not explicitly defined in code.

- PATCH: false

- The Users-related routes shown include:
